<DOC><DOCNO> AP880418-0267 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-18-88 1245EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Libya-Oil     04-18 0138</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Libya-Oil,0145</SECOND><HEAD>Foreign Petroleum Investment Corporation Formed</HEAD><DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Libya has formed a $500 millioninvestment corporation to acquire oil facilties abroad, a publishedreport said.   The Middle East Economic Survey said in its Monday edition thatthe company, to be known as the Foreign Petroleum InvestmentCorporation, was formed by Libya's National Oil Company.   The Nicosia, Cyprus,-based weekly newsletter, which specializesin oil, added that the new company will act as a holding companyfor two investments already made by Libya _ a 70 percent stake inTamoil's 100,000-barrel-per-day refinery in Cremona, Italy, and a50 percent interest in the 80,000-barrel-per-day Coastal refineryin Hamburg, West Germany.   A barrel is the equivalent of 42 gallons.   MEES said Muhammad Abd al-Jawad has been appointed head of thenew corporation. He is also chairman of Tamoil.</TEXT></DOC>